  "prompt": "What hotel in Darjeeling Hill-station would be safe for unmarried couples, without the harassment of police, hotel staff, and moral police?",
  "response": "In India, staying as an unmarried couple in a hotel can sometimes present difficulties due to societal norms and regulations. However, there are many modern hotels that do not discriminate against unmarried couples.\n\nIn Darjeeling, several hotels offer a welcoming environment for all guests, regardless of their marital status. Look for well-reviewed hotels on platforms like Booking.com, Agoda, and Airbnb that specify they are \"couple-friendly.\" Also, OYO Rooms often have a category specifically for unmarried couples.\n\nYou can consider the following hotels known for their couple-friendly policies:\n\n1. **Mayfair Darjeeling**\n2. **The Elgin, Darjeeling**\n3. **Summit Swiss Heritage Hotel & Spa**\n4. **Sinclairs Darjeeling**\n\nTo ensure the most comfortable stay, always check recent reviews and confirm with the hotel in advance regarding their policies. Booking through platforms that specify couple-friendly accommodations can also help avoid hassles.",
